							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/miafowler/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Mia-Fowler-3-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Mia-Fowler-3-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Mia Fowler" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/miafowler/">Mia Fowler</a></h6>
										Mia Fowler is an actor and writer living in Brooklyn. She maintains a <a href="https://miafowler.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://miafowler.substack.com/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1742582759888000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1yGr6C0oNYpTtzcznqcuaU" class="external">substack</a> on books, theater, and sometimes god.																			</div>
